title: Peptic ulcers
description: open sores on the inner lining of the stomach and the upper part of the small intestine

title: Ischemic Stroke
description: occurs when a blood clot, known as a thrombus, blocks or plugs an artery leading to the brain

title: Diabetic ketoacidosis (DKA)
description: is an acute, major, life-threatening complication of diabetes characterized by hyperglycemia, ketoacidosis...

title: Myocardial infarction
description: A heart attack is also called a myocardial infarction. Prompt treatment is needed for a heart attack to prevent death.

title: Acute limb ischemia (ALI)
description: a rapid decrease in lower limb blood flow due to acute occlusion of peripheral artery or bypass graft
